label.value: cranial temporal line

value.value: A dorsally concave, laterally-directed line on either side of the skull that runs along the temporal fossa, starting from above the zygomatico-frontal suture. It bounds the anterodorsal part of the temporal fossa and its the attachment site to the temporalis muscle.

label.value: euryon

value.value: An anatomical point on the most lateral point of the neurocranium.

label.value: supraorbital foramen

value.value: A bony elongated opening located above the orbit and under the forehead.

label.value: supraorbitale

value.value: An anatomical point on the median point of the line joining the aboral borders of the supraorbital foramen.

label.value: entorbitale

value.value: An anatomical point on the naso-medial indentation of the orbit that corresponds with the inner angle of the eye in the living animal.

label.value: lobular bronchiole

value.value: A conductive airway that branches into terminal bronchioles.

label.value: epithelium of lobular bronchiole

value.value: An epithelium of the lobular bronchiole.

label.value: mucosa of lobular bronchiole

value.value: A mucosa that is part of a lobular bronchiole.

label.value: smooth muscle tissue of lobular bronchiole

value.value: A smooth muscle tissue that is part of a lobular bronchiole.

label.value: visceral muscle tissue

value.value: A muscle tissue that is associated with soft internal organs (viscera).
It is quite common to refer to visceral muscles as smooth muscles, by analogy with vertebrates; however, most visceral muscles in arthropods are actually striated.

label.value: visceral smooth muscle tissue

value.value: A smooth muscle tissue that is associated with soft internal organs (viscera).

label.value: visceral striated muscle tissue

value.value: A striated muscle tissue that is associated with soft internal organs (viscera).

label.value: visceral transversely striated muscle tissue

value.value: A striated visceral muscle tissue that has a transverse striation.

label.value: visceral obliquely striated muscle tissue

value.value: A striated visceral muscle tissue that has an oblique striation.

label.value: subsegmental bronchus

value.value: Branch of conducting airway between a segmental bronchus and a preterminal bronchiole.
Like other bronchi, the walls of a subsegmental bronchus contain plates of cartilage. Notably, the cartilage plates become smaller and more widely dispersed with each branching.
